sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS number_of_users
FROM game_scores
WHERE score_value > 8;

SELECT user_id, MAX(login_date) AS latest_login
FROM user_logins
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS total_users
FROM user_feedback
WHERE feedback_type = 'bug report';

SELECT user_id, game_id, score_value
FROM game_scores
WHERE score_value > (SELECT AVG(score_value) FROM game_scores);

SELECT social_id, user_id, relationship_type
FROM user_social
WHERE relationship_type = 'friend';

external_knowledge:
- 'identities' refers to the unique identifier or user_id for each individual;
- 'personal snapshots' refers to the profile_picture_url, which is the URL to the user's profile picture;
- 'digital personas' refers to the avatar_url, which is the URL to the avatar image.

sql:
SELECT AVG(gs.score_value) AS average_score
FROM game_scores gs
WHERE gs.user_id = 1 AND gs.game_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
Active users refer to users with a status of 'active' in the system; 
The average play time skew is calculated using the arctangent function, which is often used to reduce the effect of extreme values in a dataset; 
Gaming statistics include total games played, unique locations, and average highest scores; 
Top 10 refers to the users with the highest average play time skew.
